\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.1}{\ignorespaces Schematic regime map for direct precision shrinkage. The method works well (green region) when the target aligns with the true precision structure; it fails (red region) when the target is misaligned, regardless of ensemble size. The rank-deficient regime ($N_e < n$, blue region) requires alternative methods. Our two experiments (circles) occupy opposite corners.}}{64}{figure.caption.66}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:regime_map}{{5.1}{64}{Schematic regime map for direct precision shrinkage. The method works well (green region) when the target aligns with the true precision structure; it fails (red region) when the target is misaligned, regardless of ensemble size. The rank-deficient regime ($N_e < n$, blue region) requires alternative methods. Our two experiments (circles) occupy opposite corners}{figure.caption.66}{}}
